gender.Description: gender of the participant as reported by the participant

inclusion.Description: index of participants that were included in manuscript analyses

comment.Description: Reason for exclusion and any additional notes about the participant

onset.Description: Onset time for each trial during a given training run.

duration.Description: Length of time stimulus appears on the screen.

run_num.Description: The training block or run number (there are 4 runs of training)

is_pre.Description: If the scan was conducted before training (1 = yes, 0 = no).

stim_id.Description: Unique ID number to denote which face-blend is being viewed (1-9).

relevant_blend.Description: The category-relevant parent face included in the blend.

irrelevant_blend.Description: The category-irrelevant parent face included in the blend.

relevant_category.Description: The category-relevant category (1 = Miller, 2 = Wilson, 3 = Davis)

irrelevant_category.Description: The category-irrelevant category (1 = Miller, 2 = Wilson, 3 = Davis)

README:
Title: Evaluating methods for measuring background connectivity in slow-event related fMRI designs

fMRI task where participants passively viewed blended face stimuli (nine faces total). A resting-state scan was complete prior to the passive viewing task.

Task order: rest, expo_run-1, expo_run-2, expo_run-3, expo_run-4

Information related to the task for each trial (onsets, duration of stimulus on the screen, category-relevant and category-irrelevant faces that constitute each blend) are included in a _events.tsv file for each subject and each run of the training task.
